list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment:
Fix bugs that cause: 1. Abnormally high map update quality. 2. Different map-matching result for the same map. 3. Missing match road way ID.
The current version is the first stable version after DASFAA submission. Not gonna change map-matching unless severe problem occurs.
TODO: Scalability test. Implement index-based map-matching strategy for efficiency improvement. Change co-optimisation strategy for better correctness.

findStrings.find: the inferred roads are shorter than original road

task.summary:
HMM probability check finished, influence normalization finished. Commit before map inference change
TODO: change map inference algorithm to CrowdAtlas

Trajectory preprocessing changed. Now it support partial trajectory as input. However, the ground-truth matching result deteriorates even more.
TODO: change map inference algorithm to CrowdAtlas. Refine the ground-truth map-matching result

CrowdAtlas implemented. Trajectory speed and heading are taken into consideration in map inference.
TODO: Find the bug causing the probability changes without matching to new road. Map merging improvement pending.
Map merge improvement completed. All functionality done. Ready for bulk test. TODO: Improve the combine score function and cost function for better performance. Start bulk test for all sizes of maps.

A bunch of data analysis is done. Input road ways now are categorized by road level, road type, the unfolding visualization is completely rewritten to support various color based on road visit frequency, trajectory comparison and multiple map layer. A few map-matching bugs fixed.
TODO: add confidence score and influence score, test the map merge and evaluation.

Both confidence score and influence score are added, map merge, co-optimization model and result refinement are implemented. The iteration is runnable now but the map merge need to be improved to enable a reasonable iteration. The visualization is rewritten, now it has a separate entrance for map visualization and the map and trajectory visualization is separated. The map-matching evaluation is changed to evaluate based on length.
TODO: Check the map-matching correctness, especially the top-k version. Redesign the map-merge to provide meaningful output. Change the road removal strategy.

Basic functionality complete, map merge and road removal is improved. Ground-truth map-matching reaches 98% precision and 99% recall. Start to focus on optimization
TODO: Parallel computing, more reasonable map merge

Parallel map-matching done. Able to generate ground-truth result in parallel. Matching results are written through multi-thread.
TODO: Improve map-matching logic, modify map-merge and start working on cost functions.

All components runs properly. Ready for large tests. Map-matching logic improved.
TODO: Modify map-merge and start working on cost functions.

First static version for large scale test.
TODO: Try improve the accuracy.

Ready for large scale test. The WSDM version.
TODO: Deal with the probability issue when break happens.
